# AIOS - AI-Generated Operating System

## Denote

**Project**: AIOS (AI-Generated Operating System)
**Primary Maintainer**: @joeyjiaojg
**AI Commit Email**: aios@aios.ai
**Architecture**: x86_64 (initial)
**Language**: Rust (no_std)

### Funding Purpose

This project relies heavily on AI API tokens for code generation. All sponsorship funds go directly toward:

1. **AI Model API Access**: Purchasing tokens from Claude, GPT-4, and other models
2. **Compute Infrastructure**: Running QEMU tests and AI research pipelines
3. **Model Diversity**: Accessing different models for different subsystems (e.g., Claude for kernel, GPT-4 for drivers)

### Sponsor

👉 [GitHub Sponsors: @joeyjiaojg](https://github.com/sponsors/joeyjiaojg)

### Token Budget

| Priority | Allocation |
|----------|-----------|
| Kernel core | 25% |
| Drivers | 20% |
| Filesystems | 15% |
| Network | 15% |
| Testing | 15% |
| Feature research | 10% |

---

> AIOS is an experiment in AI-driven software development. We aim to prove that an entire operating system can be built with AI-generated code.
